05:28:38.756Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Hi,\n\nWhile experimenting with parser bypass techniques, I discovered that RDoc markup could be used to inject a stored JavaScript payload into a project `README.rdoc` file.\n\nPlease note that this issue is separate to my earlier report #200565 (XSS with AsciiDoc markup), marked as duplicate.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Create a new GitLab project\n2. Initialise the project by creating a `README` file\n3. Set the file title to `README.rdoc`\n4. Paste the below Payload into the file\n5. Commit the file to the project and click on the \"XSS\" link\n\n## Proof of Concept Payload\n`XSS[JaVaScriPt:alert(1)] \u003c-- click to test`\n\nThanks!","weakness":{"id":60,"name":"Cross-site Scripting (XSS) - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2017-03-17T05:17:40.587Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-144233011.68720022,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":7,"voters":["mpz","xyodh","eveeez","sumit7","rbcafe","spetr0x","nosas"],"severity":{"rating":"medium","author_type":"User"},"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":1441094,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugTriaged","message":"Hi again @ysx,\n\nNice find! I've opened the confidential issue https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-ce/issues/27153 to discuss this vulnerability. Once a patch is available this issue will be made public and you'll be credited on our vulnerability acknowledgements page (if you wish). Do you have a preferred contact for us to publish along with the release post? We typically use HackerOne handles, Twitter, Facebook, or personal blogs.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-01-24T15:05:30.720Z","updated_at":"2017-01-24T15:05:30.720Z","actor":{"username":"briann","cleared":false,"url":"/bria